@startuml
title PDE Physical Chain - Dual SLM/Camera Capture Sequence

actor "Application" as App
participant "PDEPhysicalChain\n(Main Thread)" as PDE
participant "Worker\nThread" as Worker
participant "SLMController\n(Singleton)" as SLM
box "Hardware" #LightBlue
participant "SLM T\nHardware" as SLMT_HW
participant "SLM R\nHardware" as SLMR_HW
end box
participant "Camera 1" as Cam1
participant "Camera 2" as Cam2
participant "Frame Grabber\n(DMA Pool)" as DMA
participant "Frame\n(RAII)" as Frame

note over PDE : State: Ready\n(acquisition started,\nDMA buffers allocated)

== Capture Request ==
App -> PDE : setSLMCaptureCamera\n(slm_t_data, slm_r_data)
activate PDE
note right of PDE : State: Ready → First_SLM_write

PDE -> Worker : executeOnWorker\n(lambda with SDK calls)
activate Worker
note right of Worker : All SDK access\nserialized here\n(SDKs not thread-safe)

== Write First SLM (Transmission) ==
Worker -> SLM : writeImage(SLM_T, data)
activate SLM
note right of SLM : PCIe DMA\n(~1ms)
SLM -> SLMT_HW : DMA transfer
activate SLMT_HW
SLM --> Worker : DMA complete
deactivate SLM

Worker -> SLM : ImageWriteComplete(SLM_T)
activate SLM
note right of SLM : **CRITICAL**: Wait for\nSLM_T to stabilize\n(prevents race condition)
SLMT_HW -> SLMT_HW : pixel flip\n+ settling\n(~1ms)
SLMT_HW --> SLM : stable
SLM --> Worker : image stable
deactivate SLM
deactivate SLMT_HW

note right of PDE : State: First_SLM_write\n→ Second_SLM_write

== Write Second SLM (Reflection) ==
Worker -> SLM : writeImage(SLM_R, data)
activate SLM
note right of SLM : PCIe DMA\n(~1ms)
SLM -> SLMR_HW : DMA transfer
activate SLMR_HW
SLM --> Worker : DMA complete
deactivate SLM

SLMR_HW -> SLMR_HW : pixel flip\n+ settling\n(~1ms)

note right of PDE : State: Second_SLM_write\n→ Capture

== Hardware Trigger from SLM ==
SLMR_HW -> Cam1 : **Hardware Trigger Pulse**\n(from SLM R output)
SLMR_HW -> Cam2 : **Hardware Trigger Pulse**\n(from SLM R output)
deactivate SLMR_HW

note right of Cam1 : Built-in delay\nconfigured via\nsetTriggerDelay()
note right of Cam2 : Ensures both SLMs\nare fully settled

== Camera Capture (Zero-Copy) ==
Worker -> Cam1 : grabFrameZeroCopy()
activate Cam1
Cam1 -> DMA : capture to pool
activate DMA
note right of DMA : DMA to buffer\n(locks one buffer)
DMA --> Cam1 : ScopedBuffer
deactivate DMA

Cam1 -> Frame ** : create Frame\n(unique_ptr<ScopedBuffer>)
activate Frame
note right of Frame : Ownership transfer:\nDMA buffer → Frame

Cam1 --> Worker : Frame 1
deactivate Cam1

Worker -> Cam2 : grabFrameZeroCopy()
activate Cam2
Cam2 -> DMA : capture to pool
activate DMA
DMA --> Cam2 : ScopedBuffer
deactivate DMA

Cam2 -> Frame ** : create Frame
Cam2 --> Worker : Frame 2
deactivate Cam2

Worker --> PDE : CaptureResult\n{camera1_frame,\ncamera2_frame}
deactivate Worker

note right of PDE : State: Capture → Ready\n(ready for next capture)

PDE --> App : CaptureResult
deactivate PDE

== Frame Processing ==
activate App
note right of App : Application owns Frames\n(zero-copy access)

App -> Frame : getData(), process()
activate Frame
Frame --> App : void* (DMA buffer)
deactivate Frame

note right of App : Process both images

App -> App : Frames destroyed\n(go out of scope)
deactivate App

destroy Frame
note right of Frame : RAII destructors:\nRelease buffers\nback to DMA pool

note over DMA : Buffers available\nfor next capture

@enduml
